---
description: Keep local and remote Supabase migrations synchronized
alwaysApply: true
---

# Supabase Migrations

- Whenever a Supabase migration is added or changed, automatically apply all pending migrations to the linked remote project with `supabase db push` before considering the task complete.
- Run `supabase migration list` afterward and verify every local migration is recorded remotely.
- If the remote schema already contains a migration's objects but its history entry is missing, inspect the mismatch, repair only the confirmed history entry, then push the remaining migrations.
- Never report migration-dependent functionality as complete while local and remote migration histories differ.
